SUMMARY:ūüĆÜūüö∂‚Äć‚ôāÔłŹ THE PATH WALK & LUNCH ADVENTURE ūüö∂‚Äć‚ôāÔłŹ
 ūüĆÜ
DESCRIPTION:Try New Things in Toronto!\nūüĆÜūüö∂‚Äć‚ôāÔłŹ THE PATH WALK & 
 LUNCH ADVENTURE ūüö∂‚Äć‚ôāÔłŹūüĆÜ\nToronto‚Äôs Underground City‚Ä¶ Let‚Äôs
  Go Get Lost (On Purpose)\n\nDid you know Toronto has an entire second cit
 y beneath the city?\nWelcome to **PATH (Toronto)** ‚ÄĒ a 30-kilometre maze
  of tunnels\, walkways\, food courts\, shops\, office towers\, and hidden 
 corners connecting more than 70 buildings in the downtown core.\n\nIt‚Äôs 
 climate-controlled.\nIt‚Äôs slightly confusing.\nIt‚Äôs uniquely Toronto.\
 n\nAnd we‚Äôre going to explore it together ‚ÄĒ above ground first\, then 
 descending into the urban underworld like the confident city adventurers w
 e are.\n\n[NOW Magazine piece](https://web.archive.org/web/20220429041937/
 https://nowtoronto.com/lifestyle/health/toronto-walk-exploring-the-path-in
 -winter) about the PATH awhile back.\n\nūüĎČ **Don‚Äôt forget to join our 
 WhatsApp group** ‚Äď [CLICK HERE!](https://chat.whatsapp.com/H59mSCbsAi018
 gYANrKAnc?mode=ac_t)\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\nūüóļÔłŹ The Plan\n\nWe‚Äôll begin at 
 Wellesley Station and start by walking west. Then we‚Äôll head south and e
 ventually make our grand entrance into the PATH system.\n\nFrom there\, we
 ‚Äôll continue indoors\, weaving our way south through the network ‚ÄĒ pas
 t office towers\, hidden corridors\, and pockets of unexpected energy ‚ÄĒ 
 all the way down to **Union Station**.\n\nAt Union\, we‚Äôll head into the
  food court to grab lunch\, sit down\, and actually socialize (because tha
 t‚Äôs the point\, right?). Expect lots of conversation\, a little ‚ÄúWait
 ‚Ä¶ where are we?‚ÄĚ and a whole lot of discovering how this city secretly
  works.\nIt‚Äôs part walking tour\, part social hang\, part urban explorat
 ion.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\nūüĆßÔłŹ Rain or Shine (Mostly Shine Because‚Ä¶ Indoors)
 \nT\nhis walk goes ahead rain or shine.\nThe beauty of the PATH? We‚Äôll b
 e indoors for large portions of the route. That said\, we‚Äôll start above
  ground ‚ÄĒ so dress appropriately.\nIt may be wise to bring a backpack or
  bag for your coat once we‚Äôre inside. You don‚Äôt want to be carrying it
  dramatically over your arm like you‚Äôre in a soap opera.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\
 nūüźĺ Important Notes\nDogs are not allowed in the PATH system.\nService a
 nimals are of course welcome.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\nūüßĘ Meetup Details\nūüďć Me
 etup Spot: Main entrance of Wellesley Station\n(near the bank of PRESTO ma
 chines)\nūüęé I‚Äôll be wearing my Moose Hat\n‚Źį Start time as listed ‚ÄĒ
  please arrive on time\nWe‚Äôll begin promptly so we can stay on route.\n\
 n\\*\\*\\*\n\nūüéüÔłŹ **Meetup Fee:** $5 cash in person **or** e-transfer 
 to\nūüďß \\*\\*[mathewmaclean@hotmail.com**](http://mathewmaclean@hotmail.
 com%2A%2A/)\nThis fee helps support the group and allows us to keep hostin
 g events like this. Thank you for supporting community! ūüíĖ\n\n\\*\\*\\*\
 n\nūüĆą Who Is This For?\nThis group is open to anyone who wants to be soc
 ial and make friends ‚ÄĒ whether single or not.\n\nWe also host:\nūüé¨ Mov
 ies\nūüö∂ Walks & hikes\nūüé≠ Arts & culture outings\nūüćĹÔłŹ Restaurant m
 eetups\n\nThere‚Äôs always something happening.\nAnd remember ‚ÄĒ you can 
 just show up on the day if you‚Äôre unsure about your schedule.\n\n\\*\\*\
 \*\n‚ö†ÔłŹ A Gentle Reminder\nSometimes life throws curveballs and events 
 may need to be canceled ‚ÄĒ please keep an eye on updates.\n\n\\*\\*\\*\n\
 nūüĎ§ Organizer: Mathew\nQuestions? Post on the event wall or email\nūüďß 
 [torontomoviesandoutings@hotmail.com](mailto:torontomoviesandoutings@hotma
 il.com)\n\nCome for the tunnels.\nStay for the laughs.\nLeave knowing a se
