SUMMARY:The Good Friday Dinner and Dance Party! (with DJ and Live Band) (A
 pril 3rd)
DESCRIPTION:Try New Things in Toronto!\nGood day everyone\,\n\nPlease join
  us for a fantastic long weekend **Good Friday** night experience as we mi
 x\, mingle\, make new friends\, enjoy a tasty dinner and then dance the ni
 ght away to a fabulous Band and DJ!\n\n\\*Joined by my other social groups
  too\; so we can anticipate a terrific turn out with lots of friendly peer
 s to enjoy dinner and the game\n\n**\\*Meet us inside Smoke Show between 6
 :00 pm and 7:00 pm**\n\\*If you have to arrive after that\, still let the 
 front door guy know you are with Steve's group so he can direct you to us 
 (but kindly do your best to arrive between 6:00 pm and 7:00 pm (as I can't
  promise seating after that)-Thank you!\n(You will be paying me not the gu
 y at the front door\, so simply ask him to direct you to the group- thank 
 you!)\n\n(Event Details Below)\n\nSincerely\,\n\nSteve Flemming\n(Organize
 r/Host )\n\nEvent Details:\n**The Good Friday Dinner and Dance Party!**\n*
 *(with DJ and Live Band)**\n**(Friday April 3rd)**\n\n-A fun\, interactive
 \, event with friends\, reserved seating\, dinner\, beverages\, Live Band\
 , DJ and Dancing!\n-Pool Table available\n-DJ\, Live band and Dancing afte
 r dinner :)\n-Plenty of parking all around the venue\n\\*For more informat
 ion on the menu please refer to the Smoke Show menu https://www.smokeshowb
 bqandbrew.com/\n\n**Event Fee:**\n10 dollars (cash only) when you arrive (
 HST is included)\nor e transfer in advance to [Steveflemming11@gmail.com](
 http://Steveflemming11@gmail.com/)\n(Beverage or Appetizer Minimum please)
 \n\n**-Arrive any time between 6:00 pm and 7:00 pm inside the restaurant (
 ask or look for Steve/Organizer when you arrive)**\n\\*If arriving after 7
 :00 you still need to let the guy at the front know you are with Steve's g
 roup so he can properly direct you to us and help track our numbers- Thank
  you!\n(You will be paying me not the guy at the front door-so please let 
 him guide you to the group)\n\n(1 minute walk now from the Mt. Pleasant an
 d Eglinton station)
